<TITLE> Businessman shot dead in Bhasantek </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 11 (bdnews24.com)Unknown gunmen shot and killed a businessman on Friday noon in north Bhashantek in the capital, hours after gunmen shot a student dead in Mirpur on Thursday night. Kafrul police chief Md Delwar Hossain told bdnews24.com that at around 1pm some five miscreats rushed into Liton Furniture at Baganbarhi in Bhashantek, fired shots at random and again hurriedly left. "The owner of the mart, 45-year-old Oliullah sitting inside got hit. The locals took him to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where the duty doctors declared him dead," said the police official. Police are investigating the incident, he added. A shop-keeper was seriously injured in Mirpur half an hour after the student's killing in the latest spate of violent crimes in the neighbourhood. bd
